<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=58&amp;p=272#p272"><![CDATA[
The VRC7 <strong>is</strong> a YM2413, except it has the rhythm channels removed (and a few other bits as well) - all you need to do is compare their I/O register layouts and it's easy to see.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Wed Nov 24, 2004 12:22 am</p><hr />
